<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-03-0635 </DOCNO><TEXT>Only the plant kingdom can store solar energy by chemical process. Acock'sstudy of South Africa's rapidly deteriorating vegetation shows that thiscountry is becoming desert and that for continued existence as we knowit, immediate action is mandatory. The effects of tree planting in Chinaand Scotland and of grubbing up hedgerows in Europe show that Agroforestrysignificantly increases agricultural production. Planting windbreaksalong fence lines saves fencing, provides greater profits and employmentand sufficient fuel for our rural population.</TEXT></DOC>